<TEXT>
when ermelindo martins saw what 
looked like a giant turkey loose in rios zoo visions of a 
christmas feast overcame his good sense 
in a predawn raid tuesday martins and a friend attracted the 
longnecked bird to the fence and broke its neck as they prepared 
to load the 65pound carcass into a supermarket cart they were 
caught by the night watchman and taken to a police station 
there they learned that their victim was a rhea a rare 
ostrichlike bird from brazils central plains killing one is 
considered an ecological crime and punishable by up to six 
years in prison 
it doesnt look anything like a turkey and its meat is hard 
almost inedible said zoo spokeswoman esther nazareth 
she explained that the zoo had five now four rheas that were 
allowed to roam the grounds at night they had not been molested 
until now she said 
martins 22 and his 16yearold companion whom police did not 
identify because he is a minor said at the 17th precinct station 
that they lived in the tuiuti hill shantytown and had simply been 
looking for dinner 
were not criminals we were just hungry we thought we were 
seeing a turkey big but a turkey martins told the rio 
newspaper o globo 
