<TEXT>
the various military divisions that took part 
in operation just cause the us force that invaded panama 
include 
task force atlantic this consisted of an army battalion from 
the 7th infantry division and a battalion from the 82nd airborne 
division which was in the jungle operations training center in 
panama atlantics mission was to secure several critical sites in 
the atlanticcaribbean side of panama troops also took control of 
the prison at gamboa 
task force semper fidelis this was made up of a marine rifle 
company and a light armored infantry company marines as well as 
additional military police semper fidelis secured the bridge of 
the americas and ensured the security of howard air force base and 
its environs 
task force red this consisted of an army ranger battalion that 
parachuted into panama their mission was to take over the 
international airfield preparing it for forces from the 82nd 
airborne to land they were assisted by special forces units 
assigned to panamas southern command 
task force bayonet this consisted of a battalion from the 
armys 6th mechanized division it was supported by a platoon of 
light tanks as well as the 5th battalion of the armys 87th 
infantry bayonet provided security in panama citys central 
section and the mechanized battalion seized the comandancia the 
headquarters of the panamanian defense forces 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

