us military officials say they are not 
actively considering a major military withdrawal from east asia 
although pentagon planners recently drafted a memorandum outlining 
such a possibility 
the asahi shimbun and washington post reported this week that 
pentagon officials were considering closing us bases in the 
philippines and withdrawing forces from south korea and japan 
that policy was outlined in a paper discussed at a meeting 
monday involving defense secretary dick cheney and gen colin 
powell chairman of the joint chiefs of staff but many other 
options also were discussed pentagon officials said wednesday 
one source said that no such withdrawal was being considered for 
the next two or three years 
us pacific forces include 222238 personnel 50000 in japan 
45000 in hawaii 32000 in south korea and 34000 at sea 
according to pentagon statistics additionally the united states 
operates two important bases in the philippines 
