a federal jury convicted an alabama 
state legislator of taking money to influence legislation but 
acquitted two others of accepting bribes from a union official 
after almost three days of deliberations jurors on wednesday 
found rep pat davis guilty of four counts and innocent of four 
others reps john rogers and jim wright were found innocent on two 
counts each all three are democrats 
mrs davis refused to comment after the verdict and friends 
rushed her away from the federal courthouse 
but rogers was jubilant after the verdict yes there is a 
santa claus its the best christmas present in my life he said 
