on jan 25 the maximum possible penalty is 20 years and 250000 
on each of the four counts 
the jury convicted her of taking 12000 from a union official 
1200 for her hotel expenses during legislative sessions in 
montgomery 1000 in appreciation money and 5000 to 
reintroduce a failed coal bill 
mrs davis as were rogers and wright was acquitted of a 
conspiracy count and she was cleared of charges she took 400 to 
pay for a barbecue 500 as a christmas gift and 500 in 
fundraising money 
rogers and wright also were acquitted of charges they accepted 
5000 payments 
the government contended the three lawmakers accepted about 
30000 for their support of a bill that would have required 
