the consumer product safety commission said 
today that a stuffed animal christmas toy sold to nearly 2 million 
people may present a hidden suffocation danger to young children 
the warning involves the velveteen rabbit in a red christmas 
stocking sold from target stores in 23 states 
there is a plastic bag around the lower portion of the rabbit 
which may present a risk of suffocation to young children the 
agency said in a written statement 
consumers should remove and discard the bag immediately the 
commission said 
the bag which is not a part of the toy is inside the stocking 
and may not be immediately noticed before the toy is given to a 
child the commission said 
the floppyeared brownandwhite rabbits come in two sizes 
8inch and 12inch and the bag on the larger rabbit could easily 
fit over the head of a small child a commission staffer said 
approximately 1750000 of the toys which meet all mandatory 
and voluntary packaging and toy safety standards have been sold 
the toy rabbits were sold in missouri minnesota illinois 
michigan indiana ohio iowa oklahoma texas nevada north 
dakota south dakota colorado montana wyoming washington 
california arizona louisiana tennessee arkansas florida and 
north carolina 
