the federal budget deficit increased 2896 
billion in november raising the imbalance during the first two 
months of the fiscal year to more than half the ceiling for the 
entire year the treasury department said thursday 
combined with the october deficit of 2609 billion the 
imbalance totaled 5505 billion the grammrudman deficit 
reduction law sets a 100 billion ceiling for the fiscal year that 
began oct 1 
while the deficit is growing at a slower rate than during the 
last fiscal year it will have to slow substantially in subsequent 
months to meet the grammrudman limit 
the november deficit was 11 percent more than that posted in 
october but 06 percent less than the 2913 billion november 
imbalance a year ago 
the deficit for the first two months of fiscal 1990 was 19 
percent less than the 5614 billion recorded in octobernovember 
of fiscal 1989 
the deficit for fiscal 1989 totaled 1521 billion 
president bush on tuesday signed a deficit reduction bill that 
would trim spending by 147 billion with a goal of reducing this 
years deficit to about 103 billion according to supporters of 
the measure 
