<TEXT>
here is a brief summary of events in panama 
thousands of us troops moved into the capital on the second 
day of their offensive they encountered sporadic firing but us 
officials said their forces were in control 
president bush said the military operation was open ended 
indicating it would last as long as necessary to capture gen 
manuel antonio noriega and restore order in panama 
new president guillermo endara addressed the legislative 
assembly under heavy us guard he said he would welcome back 
members of noriegas forces who support democracy 
us troops surrounded the nicaraguan and cuban embassies with 
armored personnel carriers following rumors that noriega may have 
fled there in response nicaraguan troops in armored cars and 
tanks surrounded the us embassy in managua 
a 1 million bounty offer led to a flood of tips and rumors on 
noriegas whereabouts callers placed him in numerous locations in 
panama and in colombia the dominican republic and mexico israeli 
television reported he had been seen on the luxurious island of 
contadora off panamas coast and that he was planning to escape to 
nicaragua 
hundreds of stores in panama city were looted and their goods 
were sold on the streets of the citys slums 
the us military reported 21 soldiers and the wife of one 
us serviceman were killed 208 wounded and four missing us 
officials said 59 panamanian soldiers had been killed and 66 
wounded a doctor at a panama city hospital said 80 dead and about 
1000 injured were brought there he could give no breakdown of 
civilian and military 
