<TEXT>
the designated un envoy of the 
usinstalled government in panama said thursday that if gen 
manuel antonio noriega is captured he should not be extradited to 
the united states but tried in panama 
later thursday the 15member security council debated the 
panama invasion with many governments denouncing the united 
states but the council could not decide which government to 
recognize noriegas or the usbacked government of guillermo 
endara and no further meeting was scheduled 
both sides have sought to have their ambassadors accredited to 
the united nations which can recognize only one of them 
eduardo vallarino a selfexiled panamanian businessman was 
nominated as panamas un ambassador by endaras government 
installed by us troops at a military base wednesday 
vallarino told a news conference that panamas constitution 
prohibits extradition if noriega is captured by occupying us 
forces he said panama would protest his extradition to face 
narcotics charges in the united states 
i would have to say that probably the panamanian government 
would have to protest vallarino said in answer to a question 
if noriega is apprehended by the authorities in panama he 
will have to be duly charged and tried in panama vallarino said 
but he added that the situation is irregular 
he also said the endara group had not sought us intervention 
in panama but welcomed it 
secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar in his first comment 
on the us intervention said the position of the un for the 
last 45 years is that we always regret the use of force 
he added that he hoped the security council would reach 
agreement to restore order in panama 
he spoke before the council reconvened at the request of 
nicaragua which along with the soviet union condemned the us 
invasion wednesday night 
nicaragua seeks council condemnation of the us military 
action but the united states and britain could veto any critical 
resolution 
discussion of credentials by the security council is rare and 
has not occurred in recent memory 
the noriega government is not represented in the united nations 
because the previous envoy leonardo kam has been promoted to 
foreign minister that government is trying to accredit as un 
envoy its ambassador to the european community mirla bellavita 
un diplomats speaking on condition of anonymity said they 
expected the council would not take up the question of competing 
claims they said the council was likely to ask the 
secretarygeneral for a report the secretarygeneral however had 
said he hoped the council would decide the question 
the question ultimately could be passed on to the general 
assembly diplomats said but according to the un charter the 
159nation assembly cannot take up a question while it is under 
consideration by the council without a request by the council 
the un legal department is studying the question 
the organization of american states in washington declined to 
recognize the endara government wednesday 
vietnams invasion of cambodia in late 1978 posed a similar 
problem for the general assembly which refused to recognize the 
vietnaminstalled government and still recocognizes the ousted 
cambodian government in exile headed by prince norodom sihanouk 
and his allies 
speakers from 10 countries addressed the council thursday and 
all except el salvador denounced the us invasion although some 
also criticized noriega 
el salvador did not specifically endorse the us action but 
criticized noriegas undermining of democracy and 
selfdetermination in panama 
peru was especially vocal in condemning flagrant violation of 
panamas sovereignty in what it called a grim updating of 
imperialist practices 
other speakers included algeria brazil cuba ethiopia finland 
and libya in the first debate wednesday night only britain 
staunchly backed the us action 
