<TEXT>
here are key events in the machinists union strike against 
eastern airlines 
march 3 president bush refuses national mediation board 
request to use his authority under railway labor act to delay 
strike 60 days machinists reject easterns latest contract offer 
talks collapse at midnight 
march 4 strike begins canceling almost 90 percent of eastern 
flights stranding passengers across nation in caribbean and latin 
america 
march 5 few eastern flights take off as pilots honor the 
strike 
march 6 eastern idles 7000 nonunion workers and cancels 
nearly all flights airline asks federal judge to order pilots back 
to work 
march 7 judge refuses to order pilots back to work eastern 
furloughs another 2500 employees 
march 9 eastern files for protection from creditors under 
chapter 11 in us bankruptcy court in new york 
march 31 real estate tycoon donald trump announces he has 
completed a restructured deal to buy easterns northeast shuttle 
service for 365 million the new deal revised from an october 
1988 agreement provides him with four additional boeing 727s 
april 6 a group led by former baseball commissioner peter v 
ueberroth announces it will acquire eastern and a 199 percent 
stake in the system one reservations system in a deal valued at 
464 million under the deal with easterns parent texas air corp 
eastern employees would own 30 percent of the airline in return for 
wage and benefit concessions 
april 12 ueberroth and eastern announce the buyout proposal 
has collapsed eastern says it intends to reorganize as a smaller 
carrier serving roughly 50 percent to 60 percent of its prestrike 
schedule 
may 3 a group led by william howard former chairman of 
piedmont aviation discloses that it is interested in making a 
buyout proposal for all of eastern chicago businessman joseph 
ritchie already has expressed interest 
america west airlines offers to pay 726 million for easterns 
shuttle and 10 boeing 757s 
may 23 eastern graduates its first class of new pilots hired 
since the start of the strike 
may 25 lifland formally approves the sale of the shuttle to 
trump for 365 million after america west withdraws offer because 
of failure to arrange financing 
june 1 david shapiro bankruptcy examiner in the eastern 
case dismisses the howard groups offer 
june 2 eastern announces an austerity program for nonunion 
employees 
june 5 lifland removes the ritchie plan from consideration 
july 21 eastern submits a reorganization plan to the 
bankruptcy court creditors express approval 
early august the striking pilots vote to continue their 
sympathy walkout 
aug 24 texas air chairman frank lorenzo says he is 
considering selling all or part of continental airlines easterns 
sister carrier scandinavian airlines systems which owns 99 
percent of texas air reportedly is interested in buying a stake in 
continental 
aug 31 eastern abandons an earlier plan to sell latin 
american routes giving it around 370 million less in cash by 
yearend than first projected 
sept 8 the striking pilots vote to throw out their leader 
jack bavis for proposing that they consider ending walkout 
sept 13 lorenzo tells texas air shareholders eastern will 
turn a profit in 1990 sas says it has no immediate interest in 
buying part of continental 
nov 22 the 2250 pilots still on strike vote to end it the 
striking flight attendants quickly follow leaving the machinists 
alone on picket lines eastern says few jobs are left because its 
hired replacements 
dec 19 american airlines announces it will buy latin 
american routes and other assets from texas air for 471 million 
the deal shrinks eastern to about twothirds its prestrike size 
