<TEXT>
continued cold weather in the eastern half of 
the nation boosted energy futures sharply higher thursday 
home heating oil for january delivery shot up 405 cents to 
7981 cents a gallon on the new york mercantile exchange 
subsequent contract months also posted strong gains 
demand for heating oil has surged as temperatures plunged in 
recent days several oil companies including exxon usa mobil 
corp and texaco incs star enterprise have reported temporary 
shortages of the fuel at some of their northeast terminals 
james fiedler an oil market analyst with edampf man 
international futures inc said the cold was responsible not only 
for the jump in heating oil prices but in gasoline futures as well 
unleaded gasoline for january delivery rose 241 cents to 5563 
cents a gallon on the mercantile exchange with later months also 
rising sharply 
fiedler said traders were anticipating weatherrelated problems 
at gasoline refineries in texas where freezing temperatures have 
forced plant shutdowns in previous years refinery closings could 
make gasoline supplies tighter 
crude oil prices which often rise along with refined product 
prices continued that trend thursday west texas intermediate the 
benchmark grade of us crude rose 31 cents to settle at 2152 a 
42gallon barrel 
